&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title:&lt;/strong&gt; Data Analyst Assistant (Part-time, 20 hours/week) - Programming Focus&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; American Fork, Utah (In Office)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Brevium is a dynamic and innovative healthcare technology company located in American Fork, Utah. We specialize in providing cutting-edge solutions for healthcare practices, with a commitment to improving patient care and operational efficiency. Our team is dedicated to delivering advanced data analytics and insights to empower healthcare professionals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the data science team to understand, enhance, and maintain existing Python and SQL programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize Python for data analysis, employing libraries such as pandas, plotly, and sklearn.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute SQL queries for database retrieval, data manipulation, and integration tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in troubleshooting and debugging code-related issues in Python and SQL.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document and present analysis results using data visualization tools such as plotly, matplotlib, and Excel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Documenting code and analysis procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the development and implementation of machine learning models for predictive analysis using industry-leading tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to communicate with Sales team to know what data insights are needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current student pursuing a degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Information Science, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in data analysis, with a strong focus on extracting actionable insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Python programming language, with experience in libraries such as pandas, plotly, sklearn.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of SQL for querying databases, retrieving data, and performing data manipulation tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with data cleaning, preprocessing, and statistical methods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read, understand, and modify existing code for data analysis and visualization in Python and SQL.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Excel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intermediate to advanced python and SQL server skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with data visualization tools like plotly and matplotlib.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous exposure to working with databases and data manipulation tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with statistical analysis tools and techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational skills and ability to be self motivated.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working Hours:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• 20 hours per week (flexible schedule to accommodate academic commitments).&lt;br&gt;Compensation $20-22/hr&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;jd-section-employer&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;jd-description-text&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Assistant &lt;br&gt;About Brevium: &lt;/strong&gt;Brevium stands at the unique intersection of technology and healthcare, two of the most dynamic and impactful sectors in today&#39;s world. As a member of our team, you&#39;ll have the opportunity to be part of a fast-growing company that&#39;s making a tangible difference in people&#39;s lives. Our software doesn&#39;t just streamline processes; it actively prompts patients to return for vital health exams that can be crucial for their overall well-being. By joining Brevium, you&#39;re not just embarking on a new job; you&#39;re becoming part of a mission to enhance healthcare quality and outcomes. If you&#39;re passionate about leveraging technology for the greater good and eager to grow in a vibrant and ever-evolving environment, Brevium is the place for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team thrives on values such as integrity, innovation, continuous improvement, candor, competence, and teamwork.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mission:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support the Sales Team by identifying, researching, and qualifying potential medical practices, and contributing to the team&#39;s goal based on sign-ups from inbound/outbound requests. Assist the SDR lead and the VP of Sales and Marketing with organizing and executing company lunches, employee events, supply orders etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Entry-level position in the Sales department with potential growth opportunities into Sales Development Representative (SDR) or Account Executive (AE) roles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Outcomes:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Generation &amp;amp; Qualification:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access and mine data in Salesforce to identify potential accounts and contacts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Conduct independent research, including web searches and phone calls, to gather more information about potential accounts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ensure that the identified accounts meet the criteria of being on a supported practice management system, having more than 3+ providers, and having the name and contact of a decision-maker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Handover:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After qualifying the accounts, hand over the researched data to the Account Executive assigned.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maintain open communication to provide any additional information or clarification as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assist VP of Sales and SDR Lead with organizing company lunches, team building activities, ordering office supplies and various tasks. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tracking &amp;amp; Reporting:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Keep a record of the number of qualified accounts identified.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regularly update assigned members on progress and any challenges faced during the research process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Continuous Improvement:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stay updated with the list of supported practice management systems to ensure accurate account qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Seek feedback from the team on the quality of leads provided and make necessary adjustments to the research process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competencies:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Communication: Confident and articulate in both written and spoken interactions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Research Skills: Ability to mine databases, conduct web searches, and make phone calls to gather accurate information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team Player: Enthusiastic about working onsite and building relationships with the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Technical Proficiency: Familiar with Microsoft Word, Outlook, Excel, and the ability to learn Salesforce CRM.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Education: Some college or higher-level education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Inform

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title&lt;/strong&gt;: Sales Development Representative (SDR)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;: Onsite in American Fork, Utah&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Brevium&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brevium helps medical practices reactivate their patients with innovative technology that optimizes recall efforts, boosts patient retention, and increases revenue. Brevium&#39;s cutting-edge solutions enable healthcare providers to enhance patient care and engagement, while streamlining practice operations for better results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Day in the Life as an SDR at Brevium&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make 30-40 cold calls and send 30-40 personalized emails daily&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and add 15+ new contacts into your call cadence to build your pipeline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Account Executives to discuss and strategize methods to engage targeted accounts and setting quality meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize LinkedIn and Salesforce to identify, track, and engage prospects effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in various meetings, including 1:1s, team meetings, trainings, and sales calls, to continuously develop your sales skills and industry knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage in peer collaboration, sharing best practices, role-playing, and learning from “oops moments” to drive continuous improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain self-discipline, accountability, and reliability in all tasks and goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Success Metrics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Month 1&lt;/strong&gt;: Achieve 2 demos and engage with 10 providers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Month 2&lt;/strong&gt;: Achieve 5 demos and engage with 25 providers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Month 3&lt;/strong&gt;: Achieve 7 demos and engage with 60 providers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;0-2 years of sales experience; open to entry-level candidates with the right attitude and willingness to learn&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CRM experience is a plus (Salesforce preferred but not required)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidates with experience in summer sales or young recruiters are strongly encouraged to apply&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for being an SDR and developing into a sales professional&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Persistence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication, both written and verbal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exemplify Brevium&#39;s core values of integrity, innovation, teamwork, respectful candor, constant improvement, and competence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A start date of ASAP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation and Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base Salary&lt;/strong&gt;: $45,000 - $60,000&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On-Target Earnings (OTE)&lt;/strong&gt;: $75,000 - $100,000 depending on experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401K match: 100% match for the first 3% contributed and a 50% match for the next 2%&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health Savings Account (HSA) available&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive health, vision, dental, life (a $200K policy), and disability insurance with all premiums paid by Brevium&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optional GAP or Premium insurance plans available (employees cover difference in premiums if chosen)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quarterly bonuses based on company-wide performance goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re enthusiastic about starting or growing your sales career, thrive in a collaborative environment, and are motivated by measurable outcomes, we’d love to hear from you! Apply now to join Brevium in American Fork and make an impact in the healthcare industry.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
